{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto"]]},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/gnusto\/customstateandtraits"]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/CustomStateAndTraits"},"abstract":[{"text":"Carry your own data on entities and in globals, alongside the engine’s closed core.","type":"text"}],"kind":"article","primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Global","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" normally holds one scalar (","type":"text"},{"code":"Bool","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":"Int","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":"Double","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"String","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"), and an item or location carries only the traits the engine knows about ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"wearable"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"surface","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"dark","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", …). Those closed sets are deliberate: the engine’s behavior branches over a small, readable vocabulary you can audit at a glance. But a game system — a wallet, combat stats, an item’s price — needs to carry data the engine itself never acts on. Custom state and custom traits are the open edges beside that closed core: unlimited declarative data for your rules to read and write, boxed through the same storage the engine already saves and restores."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The split is the whole idea. "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"The engine still switches only on the closed core.","type":"text"}]},{"text":" Your custom values ride along type-erased and are only ever read by your own rule code.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Rich-Global-state","type":"heading","text":"Rich `@Global` state","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Any "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Codable & Sendable"},{"type":"text","text":" type can be a global. Conform it to "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GlobalValue"},{"text":" with an empty conformance — the default implementation JSON-boxes it into the type-erased ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/StateValue\/data(typeName:bytes:)"},{"type":"text","text":" case, so there’s nothing to hand-pack:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["struct Purse: Codable, Sendable, GlobalValue {","    var coins: Int","    var receipts: [String] = []","}","","struct MyGame: Game {","    @Global var purse = Purse(coins: 10)","    \/\/ …","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Read and write it in rules exactly like a scalar global — it participates in the turn’s commit and in save\/restore through the one world-state funnel:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["lantern.before(Intent(\"buy\")) {","    guard purse.coins >= 5 else { try refuse(\"You can't afford it.\") }","    purse.coins -= 5","    try reply(\"Sold. You have \\(purse.coins) coins left.\")","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The type needs only "},{"code":"Codable","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Sendable"},{"text":" — not ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Hashable"},{"text":". The boxed bytes are what participate in the world state’s equality and hashing.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"style":"note","name":"Note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A custom global is stored as opaque bytes, so if you change its shape, an old save may no longer decode — the global then falls back to its declared default. Keep plugin\/system state structs additive and optional-tolerant (new fields with defaults), and you’ll stay compatible. Versioned codecs are a later effort."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"aside"},{"level":2,"text":"Custom traits","anchor":"Custom-traits","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Declare a typed key once, then use it to declare a custom property inside an "},{"code":"Item { … }","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"code":"Location { … }","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" block with "},{"code":"trait(_:_:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". The value is boxed with the same rule as a "},{"code":"@Global","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", so a scalar or a whole struct both work:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["extension TraitKey<Int> { static let price = Self(\"price\") }","extension TraitKey<String> { static let region = Self(\"region\") }","","let lantern = Item {","    name(\"brass lantern\")","    trait(.price, 5)","}","","let docks = Location {","    name(\"The Docks\")","    trait(.region, \"waterfront\")","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Read it back on the live proxy with the typed subscript, which returns "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":" when the trait is absent or stored as a different type:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["let price = lantern[.price] ?? 0"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A key declared with a default (","type":"text"},{"code":"TraitKey(\"weight\", default: 1)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":") can be read as a non-optional ","type":"text"},{"code":"V","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" through ","type":"text"},{"code":"item[default: .weight]","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instead.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Custom traits are ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"immutable declared facts","type":"text"}]},{"text":" — they never touch the world state. For per-entity state that ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"changes"}]},{"type":"text","text":" during play (an item’s current charge, a creature’s HP), use a "},{"code":"@Global","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" keyed however your system needs; traits are for the fixed properties an entity is born with."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Closed core, open edges","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Closed-core-open-edges"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The engine never switches on a custom trait or a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".data"},{"type":"text","text":" global — it only branches over the closed "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/ItemTrait"},{"text":"\/","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/LocationTrait","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" kinds and scalar "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/StateValue","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" cases it acts on ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"isSurface"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"isWearable"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"dark"},{"type":"text","text":", …). That’s what keeps the engine auditable: every behavior it drives is still visible in a handful of small enums, while your systems get unlimited declarative properties that only your rules interpret."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"text":"Worked example","anchor":"Worked-example","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Tests\/GnustoTests\/Support\/CustomStateGames.swift"},{"type":"text","text":" builds "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ShopGame"},{"type":"text","text":": a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Purse"},{"type":"text","text":" struct held in a "},{"code":"@Global","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", a lantern with a ","type":"text"},{"code":"trait(.price, 5)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", and a game-defined ","type":"text"},{"code":"buy","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" verb whose rule reads the price and debits the purse — the commerce plugin in miniature. ","type":"text"},{"code":"CustomStateTests","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" boots it and confirms the struct global round-trips through save\/restore, the custom trait reads back through the typed subscript, and absent\/wrong-type reads return ","type":"text"},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"text":"See also","anchor":"See-also","type":"heading"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/WritingRules","type":"reference"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Plugins"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Global","isActive":true}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GlobalValue","isActive":true}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"}],"kind":"content"}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"title":"Custom State and Traits","identifiers":["doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Global","doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GlobalValue","doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/StateValue"],"generated":true,"anchor":"Custom-State-and-Traits"}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"sections":[],"metadata":{"role":"article","title":"Custom State and Traits","modules":[{"name":"Gnusto"}],"roleHeading":"Article"},"references":{"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/StateValue/data(typeName:bytes:)":{"abstract":[],"type":"topic","title":"StateValue.data(typeName:bytes:)","fragments":[{"text":"case","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"data","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"typeName","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"String","preciseIdentifier":"s:SS","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"bytes","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Data","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:10Foundation4DataV"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/statevalue\/data(typename:bytes:)","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/StateValue\/data(typeName:bytes:)"},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/WritingRules":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Attach game logic to items, locations, and the world."}],"type":"topic","title":"Writing Rules","kind":"article","role":"article","url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/writingrules","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/WritingRules"},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/GlobalValue":{"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"GlobalValue"}],"role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GlobalValue","title":"GlobalValue","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"GlobalValue"}],"url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/globalvalue","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Types usable with the "},{"code":"@Global","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" property wrapper."}]},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/LocationTrait":{"title":"LocationTrait","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/LocationTrait","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A single fact about a location, stated inside a "},{"code":"Location { … }","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" block."}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"LocationTrait"}],"url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/locationtrait","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"LocationTrait","kind":"identifier"}]},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/Global":{"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Custom game state with the same ergonomics as built-in state:","type":"text"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Global"}],"type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Global"}],"url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/global","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Global","title":"Global"},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/Plugins":{"role":"article","kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Plugins","title":"Plugins","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/plugins","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Package a reusable game system as an importable unit of verbs and rules."}]},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto":{"role":"collection","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto","type":"topic","title":"Gnusto","url":"\/documentation\/gnusto","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A Swift engine for writing parser-driven interactive fiction — text adventures in the tradition of Zork and Infocom’s ZIL."}]},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/StateValue":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"StateValue"}],"abstract":[{"text":"A value that can live in ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"WorldState"},{"text":"’s global storage. The scalar cases","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"each pair with a dedicated "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GlobalValue"},{"type":"text","text":" conformance; "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/StateValue\/data(typeName:bytes:)","isActive":true},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"is the type-erased case that carries any other "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Codable"},{"type":"text","text":" value, so custom"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"state structs and custom traits need no new case of their own.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/StateValue","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"StateValue","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"StateValue","url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/statevalue","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","role":"symbol"},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/ItemTrait":{"title":"ItemTrait","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/ItemTrait","abstract":[{"text":"A single fact about an item, stated inside an ","type":"text"},{"code":"Item { … }","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" block."}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"ItemTrait","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/itemtrait","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"ItemTrait"}]}}}